    </div>
    <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/sej.1399" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Read the paper ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">The Dark Side of Junior Stock Exchanges</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Market catalysts — incubators, science parks, junior stock exchanges — are designed to stimulate venture creation. Analysis of 19,000 firms in Japan shows they can produce unintended negative consequences: more competition and information asymmetry, ultimately fewer quality IPOs and less economic growth. Stanford eCorner conversation with Bob Eberhart on their <em>Strategic Management Journal</em> paper, 2018.
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/OHPmRQYploA"
